void JVMc_getFileFromJarResponse (  JarExtractId  extrationId,
void *  fileData,
UINT32  fileSize
) 
 

JVMc_getFileFromJarResponse is called to request extraction of a specific file from a JAR file. The answer to this function should be supplied in JVMc_getFileFromJarResponse. The memory supplied in the parameters must be copied if it will be used after this function has returned.

Parameters:
extractionId This is the requested number from JVMa_getFileFromJar
fileData The file itself. The memory area will be deleted when the function returns. If NULL, then an error has occurred.
fileSize The size of the received file.
